author: Inside Edition
description: Police say a group of kids were playing ding dong ditch around 11 p.m. in Houston. Ding Dong Ditch is a prank in which kids ring a doorbell or knock on the door then run away before anyone can answer. Police say someone came out of a home and opened fire and one of the boys, who was 11 years old, was shot in the back. Julian Guzman died in the hospital. The boy's mother says he was "affectionate, loving," and "always smiling." Gonzalo Leon Jr., 42, has been charged with murder.
title: Ding Dong Ditch Prank Turns Deadly, 11-Year-Old Boy Killed

author: Inside Edition
description: A baby was born during a torrential rainstorm, and the mom says she didn't know she was pregnant. Kasey Thompson tells Inside Edition's Alison Hall he was sleeping in his RV in Nevada's Black Rock Desert when his wife woke up in excruciating pain. The baby girl, Aurora,  had to be airlifted to a hospital in Reno. Aurora is the couple's first child and the shocking birth happened during their first trip to Burning Man.
title: Woman Unexpectedly Gives Birth at Burning Man

author: Inside Edition
description: General Hospital's soap star Steve Burton is at the center of a real-life romance scam. Abigail Ruvalcaba, 66, says she was tricked into thinking the actor was in love with her so she gave up her life savings after receiving a fake AI-generated video of what looked like Burton telling her he loved her. Ruvalcaba's daughter headed to a Los Angeles courthouse to stop her mother from being evicted. The General Hospital star says he would never ask fans for money.
title: 'General Hospital' Actor’s AI Likeness Used to Scam Woman out of $81K

author: Inside Edition
description: A 20-year-old West Point cadet and his father dragged an injured man from his wrecked car moments before the car burst into flames. On Saturday, Army Cadet Larry Pickett Jr. played safety for the Army's Black Knights football team, then went for dinner in Times Square with his family. They came across the wreck on their way back to West Point. Larry Pickett Sr. couldn't be more proud of his son. The Secretary of the Army praised the army cadet's "extraordinary courage and selflessness."
title: 20-Year-Old Army Cadet Saves Man from Car Wreck Moments Before Fire

author: Inside Edition
description: Steven Goncalves is the brother of Kaylee Goncalves, one of the four roommates murdered by Bryan Kohberger at the University of Idaho. His fiance is Olivia Vitale and she is a journalist who covered the quadruple murder for her true-crime YouTube channel "Chronicles of Olivia." She also interviewed Steven for the Peacock documentary "The Idaho Student Murders." Now the couple has a joint YouTube channel. They spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Victim's Brother Engaged to Idaho Murder Case Journalist #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: They may look out of place to us humans, but these stuffed, robotic rabbits are supposed to attract predators, specifically the Burmese python, which officials say is wreaking havoc on the Florida Everglades. Officials say the pythons are not native to the region, but have become established in Everglades National Park because of the escape or release of pet pythons. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Robotic Rabbits Used to Lure Pythons From Hiding Spots in the Everglades
